Peacekeepers<br>
Karana chapter</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uwarriorrmog.showPublicProfile?language=EN>WarriorRmog</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(8/7/01 2:15:12 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: LFG in PoG</span><hr size=1> I posted something on The Chosen Ones boards.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CBC6B1><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/umananin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mananin</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=  http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif  BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>CoG Companion</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(8/8/01 12:55:44 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: LFG in PoG</span><hr size=1> Now I'm no expert on Growth, but here is what I can tell you:<br>
<br>
There is only one guardian at the zone-in point.  It is called a whorl of natural energy, and SOMETIMES it DOES see invis.  Somebody with invis and not kos needs to zone in and check if this is the case.  If he can see invis, it is a LOT harder to break in, because the whorl will usually grab a wandering mob or two. The zone-in is in the southwest part of the zone, and in this section roam the unicorns (drop wizzy-armor) and a wolfie (cleric armor) every now and then.  Farstride Unicorns CAN see invis, so be carefull.  There sometimes is a named unicorn that hangs around here, and she drops random leg-armor.  If anyone KOS zones in, the 2 POGS will immediately start tracking them down, so expect them in about 1 minute, and they WILL find you.<br>
<br>
There is a little ledge on the south wall near the southwestern corner where you want to set up your first camp.  The best way to get there is head west from the zone in and then south to the corner, and then a little east and you will see it.  As you run there, try to avoid any mobs in the way.  It is not very crowded, so this isn't that hard.  Be prepared to fight, because the POGs are coming.  I'm pretty sure they can't be messed either.  One way to deal with the pogs is to have someone kite them until you are ready, a monk or bard being the best.  These suckers run fast, so be carefull.<br>
<br>
After you kill three or four mobs in this area, it is fairly safe for others to zone in without training.  I think the whorl spawns every 30 mins, but you can always pull it, and it's not that hard to kill (relatively).  Also, as you probably know, the PoGs respawn in a little under half an hour, so always always time your pulls to this clock.  Designate someone to time the PoGs and announce 10 mins in advance when they will be coming.  It doesn't have to be exact, but you don't want these two bad-boys crashing the party.  At the 5 minute mark you'll want to be finished fighting.  It's a good time to rest and med up while waiting for Tweedle-dee and Tweedle-dum.<br>
<br>
Eventually the southwest area is going to be clear of mobs, so it's time to move the camp.  A good bet is to head either north or east along the wall.  Heading north will take you to more plains area, and you will see bears (shammy armor) and kodiaks (enchanter armor and monk?), along with wolfies and unicorns.  Stop about halfway to the north wall and set up camp.  Heading east takes you to a walled-pagoda with a really big armor-dude inside.  This guy is not someone to mess with, so take my word for it and keep a good distance away from the pagoda walls.  You'll see a lake beyond it, follow the shore left until you get to the river and set up camp where the river meets the lake.  This is a forested area, and wolfies and plants (warrior and rogue? armor) roam around here, as well as the occasional unicorn.  Treah sometimes appears too.  Unless you really know what you are doing, don't pull her.  Can you say over 200000hps, and hits for 700?  And she throws off something like an ice comet every now and then too.  Oh, and she summons all her little sylvan protectors to help cater the party,  unless you've killed them all beforehand.<br>
<br>
Most mobs seem to be standard warrior types, however, there is one mob you need to be really carefull when fighting, and those are tranquil treants.  These fools will gate on you, then they will summon everyone one-by-one and kill you all off.  When fighting them, all melees need to be on one side, so that their hits can push the little tree back and interrupt it's gate.  This may be the only way to prevent them from gating.  If the little guy gates, you gotta camp and hope for the best.<br>
<br>
As we all know, things sometimes go bad, so bring about 1 cleric per party on the raid.  You can get away with less if one has a click-stick, but you'll need to rez really fast.<br>
<br>
From what I've seen, you could do a fair raid with two groups 55+ or four groups 50+.  You won't be killing Treah, and you should probably stay away from the wisps (northeastern area), but you'll be able to pick up armor and 55 spells and gems.  Now I was spoiled and went with rez-mistress Ikada and a lot of really good players from Shadowed Fates and Harbingers (thanks guys!).  These people made it look easy, with their combination of experience, levels, and equipment (lots of epics).  Seeing them in action is impressive to say the least.  So on your first forays into Growth, definitely err on the side of caution.  If you can't get enough clerics or melees, don't hesitate to call off the raid.  Otherwise you'll be setting yourself up for a lot of pain.<br>
<br>
I'm interested in attending this raid.  Hopefully I won't have to work that night.  I'll pass the word on to my guild too.  If I don't see you then, good luck!<br>
